# Where Do Veteran Job Candidates Live?

<a href="/attachments/regional_map_8_27_10.pdf" style="float: right; margin: 0 0 2em 1em" title="Regional populations of job candidates who are registered at recruitmilitary.com"><img src="/attachments/regional_map_08_27_10.png" alt="Regional populations of job candidates who are registered at recruitmilitary.com" width="300" height="395" /></a>

RecruitMilitary's nationwide database of job candidates with military backgrounds has become so large that employers, franchisors, and educational institutions can recruit from it confidently for positions anywhere. As the table and chart in the map in this article indicate, we have large numbers of candidates in all regions of the continental United States. Add to this the fact that our database is growing at a rate of about 20% per year.

Our database has large concentrations of veterans in the Southeast, South Central, and Pacific Southwest regions. Underlying the latter two concentrations are the dominant populations of Texas and California, respectively. Florida leads, but does not dominate, the Southeast.

How do the concentrations of veterans in our database compare with the general population? We have listed below the percentages on the map and the percentages of the general population, regardless of age. We base the latter percentages on government estimates of the 2009 population.

