As you will note, there are high concentrations of veteran candidates, relative to the general population, in the Mid-Atlantic and Southeast regions of the continental United States. Such concentrations are low in the Northeast, Midwest, and Plains regions.

Where veteran-candidates concentrations are low relative to the general population, recruiters may face stronger competition for the candidates. Other factors to consider include (1) regional unemployment rates and (2) concentrations of competing businesses in the various regions.

